review I never thought I'd do this, but I HATED this book. The last 70 pages were nothing less than painful for me to read, as I (by that time) had finally c I never thought I'd do this, but I HATED this book. The last 70 pages were nothing less than painful for me to read, as I (by that time) had finally come to the decision that there would be no plot or even the remotest chance of a story-line. There was no entertainment, no education, and extremely little enlightenment (5 one-liners, to be exact). For a book that is billed as being a "philosophical fable", that's precious little. This book is about a 12 year old spoiled brat who has absolutely nothing good to say about anyone or anything. I thought, as I read, that that would change -- it didn't. Descriptions such as "fat cow" and "pig" are common-place in describing almost everyone she deals with. I grew weary of that after about the third chapter (and there are about 80 chapters in the book). On the cover you'll find the words "New York Times Bestseller" - as I read those words, I lose faith in whomever had the nerve to like this book to elevate it to such a lofty status. It is deplorable. I'd like to say I'm proud that I finished it, but the only redeeming grace in that is to serve as a warning for others. This book sucked. I cannot stress that enough. ...more
